<paragraph blockId="4.[211,1172,207,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
Length (excluding uropods) 
<quantity box="[532,633,207,231]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="4.68">4.68 mm</quantity>
, maximum width across pereomere 4, 
<quantity box="[1066,1167,207,231]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.96" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="2.96">2.96 mm</quantity>
, head length 
<quantity box="[358,463,239,263]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.30 mm</quantity>
, head width 
<quantity box="[618,723,239,263]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.32" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="1.32">1.32 mm</quantity>
, pereon length 
<quantity box="[907,1012,239,263]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.13" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="2.13">2.13 mm</quantity>
, pleon length 
<quantity box="[211,316,271,295]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
, sinistral distortion 40 
<superScript attach="left" box="[578,587,267,284]" fontSize="7" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">◦</superScript>
. Pereomeres distinct, but separation of pleomeres obscure. No pigmentation (
<figureCitation box="[518,669,303,327]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Figure 2A, B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[211,1172,207,391]" lastBlockId="5.[143,1104,167,925]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="134" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
Head expanded and rounded anteriorly, tapered anteriorly, with well-developed frontal lamina, extending anterolaterally. Eyes absent (
<figureCitation box="[833,955,367,391]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
). Antenna of three articles, terminal one setose, antennule lacking (
<figureCitation box="[680,798,167,191]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
). Maxilliped bearing stout, triangular non-articulating palp extending prominently forward, lacking setae; plectron short and sharply tapered (
<figureCitation box="[503,624,231,255]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
). Barbula (
<figureCitation box="[750,864,231,255]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2E</figureCitation>
) with two prominent pointed falcate lateral projections on each side, outer one distinctly larger than inner; large tubercle medial to inner falcate projection and broad shorter tubercle medial to those.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" startId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" targetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[211,1172,1513,1681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
Figure 2. 
<taxonomicName authority="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li, 2011" authorityName="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[316,488,1513,1535]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sheni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[316,488,1513,1535]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Megacepon sheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[496,574,1513,1534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,1104,167,925]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
Pereon broadest across pereomere 4, gradually tapering anteriorly and posteriorly. Coxal plates absent. Pereomeres 3–5 with small mid-dorsal projections, pereomere 6 with prominent mid-dorsal projection, pereomere 7 recessed under pereomere 6, lacking projection. Dorsolateral bosses on pereomeres 1–4, and tergal projections only on left side of pereomeres 2–4 (
<figureCitation box="[513,636,486,510]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
). Oostegites completely enclosing highly vaulted brood pouch (
<figureCitation box="[406,527,518,542]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
). First oostegite (
<figureCitation box="[736,894,518,542]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2F, G</figureCitation>
) with ovate anterior segment and elongate subquadrate posterior segment, anterior segment smoothly rounded anteriorly, with slightly digitate internal ridge bearing five short lobes of various widths, posterior segment expanded at mid-length of lateral margin, tapering to rounded posterior tip. Last pair of oostegites smooth, lacking tubercles. Pereopods subequal, with all articles distinct and each article of nearly same size on all pereopods; all dactyli small and blunt (
<figureCitation box="[450,593,709,733]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2H, I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,1104,167,925]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
Pleomere 1 distinct with prominent narrow triangular mid-dorsal projection, pleomeres 2–5 apparently fused into one piece without any projections. Five pairs of biramous pleopods and lateral plates. Lateral plates, exopodites and endopodites of similar size and structure, with surfaces tuberculate and margins highly digitate (
<figureCitation box="[151,261,869,893]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2J</figureCitation>
). Uniramous uropods similar to structure of pleopods and lateral plates but shorter than lateral plates of pleomere 5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,454,999,1023]" box="[143,454,999,1023]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis box="[143,454,999,1023]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[306,394,999,1023]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">allotype</typeStatus>
male
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,1104,1039,1350]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
Length 
<quantity box="[231,331,1039,1063]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.31" pageId="5" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="2.31">2.31 mm</quantity>
, maximal width across pleon 3, 
<quantity box="[689,790,1039,1063]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="0.46">0.46 mm</quantity>
, head length 
<quantity box="[938,1039,1039,1063]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="0.16">0.16 mm</quantity>
, head width 
<quantity box="[214,315,1071,1095]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
, pleonal length 
<quantity box="[493,594,1071,1095]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="0.51">0.51 mm</quantity>
. All body segments distinct (
<figureCitation box="[915,1067,1071,1095]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2K, L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,1104,1039,1350]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
Head semicircular, eyes lacking (
<figureCitation box="[552,672,1102,1126]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2K</figureCitation>
). Antenna of three articles, distal ones setose; antennule of five articles, extending beyond the margin of head (
<figureCitation box="[942,1067,1134,1158]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2M</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,1104,1039,1350]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
Pereomeres near subequal in width, with truncate margins. All pereomeres with prominent mid-ventral tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[525,645,1198,1222]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2L</figureCitation>
). Pereopods subequal in size, all articles distinct (
<figureCitation box="[241,393,1230,1254]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2N, O</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,1104,1039,1350]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
Pleon of six pleomeres, first three with mid-ventral tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[860,976,1262,1286]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2L</figureCitation>
). Five pairs of uniramous tuberculiform pleopods, progressively smaller posteriorly. Pleomere 6 bearing uniramous lobes similar in structure and placement to pleopods (
<figureCitation box="[975,1091,1326,1350]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[211,278,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-73@4.[211,1171,435,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Megacepon sheni sp. nov. Holotype female (A–J): (A) dorsal view; (B) ventral view; (C) antenna; (D) left maxilliped, external view; (E) left side of barbula; (F) left oostegite 1, external view; (G) left oostegite 1, internal view; (H) left pereopod 1; (I) left pereopod 7; (J) left pleopod 1. Allotype male (K–O): (K) dorsal view; (L) ventral view; (M) right antennae; (N) left pereopod 2; (O) left pereopod 6. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.26 mm (C, K, L); 0.52 mm (D–J); 0.21 mm (M–O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200487/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Figure 2L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,263,1424,1448]" box="[143,263,1424,1448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis box="[143,263,1424,1448]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,1103,1464,1552]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
The specific name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[349,405,1464,1488]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sheni">
<emphasis box="[349,405,1464,1488]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">sheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is selected to honour Prof. Jia-rui Shen (1902–75), for his contributions to the research of Crustacea in 
<collectingCountry box="[608,681,1496,1520]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">China</collectingCountry>
. It is also the species name of the host crab.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,386,1626,1650]" box="[143,386,1626,1650]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis box="[143,386,1626,1650]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Distribution and hosts</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[143,872,1666,1690]" box="[143,872,1666,1690]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
<collectingRegion box="[143,333,1666,1690]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Hainan province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[344,416,1666,1690]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">China</collectingCountry>
, infesting 
<taxonomicName authority="Gordon, 1931" authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1931" box="[530,869,1666,1690]" class="Malacostraca" family="Varunidae" genus="Metaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sheni">
<emphasis box="[530,701,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Metaplax sheni</emphasis>
Gordon, 1931
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[211,309,168,192]" box="[211,309,168,192]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis box="[211,309,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[211,1172,207,773]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">
The lack of antennules on the 
<typeStatus box="[574,674,207,231]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">holotype</typeStatus>
may not be a species character but rather specific to this specimen. Lack of antennules, or even both antennae and antennules, has been reported in other bopyrids (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Markham JC" box="[698,934,271,295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" pagination="151 - 197" refId="ref5112" refString="Markham JC. 2010. The isopod parasites (Crustacea: Isopoda: Bopyridae) of decapod Crustacea of Queensland, Australia, with descriptions of three new species. Davie PJF, Phillips JA. editors. Proceedings of the Thirteenth International Marine Biological Workshop, The Marine Fauna and Flora of Moreton Bay, Queensland. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum - Nature. 54 (3): 151 - 197." type="journal article" year="2010">Markham 2010: 168</bibRefCitation>
) but has never been used to distinguish species within the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="George" authorityYear="1947" box="[717,844,304,327]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[717,844,304,327]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Megacepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Bourdon and Stock (1979" authorityName="sensu Bourdon and Stock" authorityYear="1979" box="[241,853,335,359]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goetici">
<emphasis box="[241,368,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Megacepon</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis box="[417,554,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">goetici sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bourdon R &amp; Stock JH" box="[561,853,335,359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" pagination="205 - 218" refId="ref4759" refString="Bourdon R, Stock JH. 1979. On some Indo-West Pacific Bopyridae (Isopoda, Epicaridea) in the collections of the Zoologisch Museum, Amsterdam. Beaufortia. 28 (351): 205 - 218." type="journal article" year="1979">Bourdon and Stock (1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bourdon and Stock" authorityYear="1979" box="[908,1022,336,359]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goetici">
<emphasis box="[908,934,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[950,1022,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">goetici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1029,1164,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1029,1164,336,359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, see below) as well as to 
<taxonomicName authority="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li, 2011" authorityName="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[482,740,367,391]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disparatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[482,740,367,391]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Megacepon disparatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[747,835,367,390]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, described below. All three of these taxa have males with short pleotelson anterolateral projections and females with two long falcate projections on the lateral margins of the barbula. 
<taxonomicName authority="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li, 2011" authorityName="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[946,1135,431,455]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sheni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[946,1135,431,455]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Megacepon sheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="6" pageNumber="135" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bourdon and Stock" authorityYear="1979" box="[560,716,462,486]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goetici">
<emphasis box="[560,586,463,486]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">M</emphasis>
. aff. 
<emphasis box="[644,716,463,486]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">goetici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by absence of medial boss on pereomere 5 of the female (present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bourdon and Stock" authorityYear="1979" box="[514,671,494,518]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goetici">
<emphasis box="[514,540,495,518]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">M</emphasis>
. aff. 
<emphasis box="[599,671,495,518]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">goetici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), differently shaped oostegite 1 (inner mediolateral projection of anterior segment not tapered in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[832,932,526,550]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sheni">
<emphasis box="[832,858,527,550]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[876,932,526,550]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">sheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, digitations on ridge much smaller in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[407,507,558,582]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sheni">
<emphasis box="[407,507,558,582]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">M. sheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and male with only three mid-ventral pleonal tubercles (
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bourdon and Stock" authorityYear="1979" box="[220,377,590,614]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Megacepon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goetici">
<emphasis box="[220,246,591,614]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">M</emphasis>
. aff. 
<emphasis box="[305,377,591,614]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">goetici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with five tubercles). This new species can be distinguished from 
